
ScaffMatch 0.9 INSTALLATION README

1. SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

ScaffMatch is designed to be run on GNU/Linux.

2. SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS

    * Python 2.7.x
    * Bash >= 4
    * Networkx >= 1.7
    * Numpy >= 1.6.2
    * Bowtie2

Python2.7 can be downloaded from:
     https://www.python.org/.
Bash is supposed to be installed on GNU/Linux systems. In case you have an older version, you should update it.
Networkx python library can be installed using the command:
    # pip install networkx
The instructions for installing Numpy python library can be found here:
    http://www.numpy.org/
Bowtie2 can be downloaded from:
    http://sourceforge.net/projects/bowtie-bio/files/bowtie2/

3. INSTALLATION

To download the ScaffMatch source code (the latest version), type (Git is supposed to be installed on your system):
    # git clone https://github.com/mandricigor/ScaffMatch.git
    # cd ScaffMatch

To run the installation script, run the following command:
    # sh install.sh

ScaffMatch will be installed in your /usr/bin directory.


